    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 20</em>, <em>Pathfinder Campaign Setting pg. 209</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 33</em>, <em>Advanced Player's Guide pg. 178</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 20 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 8 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> 19-20/x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> S; <strong>Special</strong> trip</p><p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Blades, Heavy</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>This heavy blade has a convex curve near the end, making its overall shape similar to that of a battleaxe. A typical khopesh is 20 to 24 inches in length. Its curved shape allows the wielder to hook around defenses and trip foes. The elegant shape of a khopesh leads some artisans to cover them in ornate decorations.</p>",
